## API Endpoints Summary

| Base Path | Resource | Key Operations |
|---|---|---|
| `/invoices` | Invoices | Create, list, get by ID, get by number, update, delete |
| `/customers` | Customers | CRUD, profile lookup, statement, PDF/Excel export |
| `/payment` | Payments | Process customer payments |
| `/return` | Returns | Process product returns with refunds |
| `/stock` | Stock | Stock management & adjustments |
| `/product` | Products | Product catalog CRUD |
| `/categories` | Categories | Hierarchical category CRUD |
| `/supplier` | Suppliers | Supplier directory CRUD |
| `/sales` | Sales Orders | Sales tracking |
| *(not mounted)* | Purchase Orders | CRUD + receive items + supplier payments + cancel |

> [!WARNING]
> The **Purchase Order routes** ([purchaseOrder.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/routes/purchaseOrder.routes.js)) are defined but **not mounted** in [app.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/app.js). The same applies to routes/controllers for **prescriptions**, **expenses**, **cash transactions**, and **reports** — their controllers exist but have no corresponding route files or aren't wired up.

---

## Core Architecture Patterns

### 1. CRUD Factory
[crudFactory.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js) provides reusable [getAll](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#99-128), [getOneById](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#50-67), [getOneByField](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#68-98), [createOne](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#38-49), [updateOne](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#19-37), [deleteOne](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/crudFactory.js#5-18) handlers. Controllers compose these with custom model-specific logic.

### 2. API Features
[features.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/utils/features.js) implements chainable query building: **filtering** (with MongoDB operators), **sorting**, **field selection**, and **pagination**.

### 3. Error Handling
- [AppError](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/utils/appError.js) — custom operational error class
- [catchAsync](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/utils/catchAsync.js) — wraps async controllers to forward errors
- [globalError.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/controllers/globalError.js) — central handler with dev (full stack) vs prod (clean message) modes; handles CastError, duplicate keys, validation errors, and JWT errors

### 4. MongoDB Transactions
Complex operations (returns, invoices, payments) use **MongoDB sessions** to ensure atomicity across multiple collection updates.

### 5. Auto-Increment Sequences
[getNextSequence.js](file:///c:/Users/Mohamed%20Elafandy/Desktop/cmder/payment/utils/getNextSequence.js) uses a `Counter` model with `findOneAndUpdate` + `$inc` for generating sequential numbers (invoice numbers, order numbers, etc.).

---

## Data Model Relationships

```mermaid
erDiagram
    Customer ||--o{ Invoice : "has"
    Customer ||--o{ Payment : "makes"
    Customer ||--o{ Return : "requests"
    Customer ||--o{ Transaction : "has"
    Invoice ||--o{ Return : "has"
    Invoice }o--|| Customer : "belongs to"
    Invoice ||--|{ InvoiceItem : "contains"
    InvoiceItem }o--|| Product : "references"
    Product }o--|| Category : "belongs to"
    Product }o--|| Supplier : "supplied by"
    Product ||--|| Stock : "tracked in"
    Return }o--|| Product : "for"
    Payment }o--o| Invoice : "applied to"
    PurchaseOrder }o--|| Supplier : "from"
    PurchaseOrder ||--|{ PurchaseItem : "contains"
    PurchaseOrder ||--o{ SupplierPayment : "paid via"
    Prescription }o--|| Customer : "for"
    Prescription ||--|{ PrescriptionItem : "contains"
    Prescription }o--o| Invoice : "linked to"
    Category }o--o| Category : "parent"
    SalesOrder }o--|| Customer : "for"
    SalesOrder }o--|| Product : "sells"
```

---

## Key Business Logic

### Invoice Creation
The largest controller (~33KB). Creates invoices by: validating items, looking up products, calculating totals (subtotal + tax - discount), deducting stock, creating sales records, recording transactions, updating customer balances — all within a MongoDB transaction.

### Return Processing
Validates the return against the original invoice, checks previously returned quantities, calculates refund amounts, restores stock, updates the invoice's totals and balance, creates refund transactions, and adjusts customer balances — all atomic via MongoDB session.

### Payment Processing  
Records payments, updates invoice `amountPaid` and `balanceDue`, triggers status changes (partially_paid → paid), and reconciles customer outstanding balances.

### Purchase Order Lifecycle
Full workflow: create → receive items (partial/full) → supplier payments → cancel. Receiving items auto-updates stock quantities. Pre-save hooks automatically compute `paymentStatus` and `status`.

### Prescription Management
Pharmacy-specific: tracks doctor info, dosage, frequency, duration, insurance requirements, and expiry. Links to invoices when dispensed.

